summaries.short: The #2 seeded Panthers take on the #1 seed for the most important match-up of the season and a possible place in the national championship.
summaries.full: With week two's home opener against Simeon fast approaching, the #2 seeded Panthers use the game as an opportunity to prepare for their highly anticipated upcoming showdown against top-ranked Mater Dei. As top players manage high expectations, Baltimore City Council president Brandon Scott gives the Panthers a pep talk before they take the field.

summaries.short: Host Victor Cruz reflects on the strength it takes to succeed in difficult situations; later, he speaks with Dr. Jessica Clemons.
summaries.full: Host Victor Cruz reflects on the mental and emotional strength it takes to succeed in difficult situations and the ways in which both he and the St. Frances Academy players had to overcome everyday trauma. Victor then speaks with leading mental health professional, psychiatrist Dr. Jessica Clemons about the importance of taking care of our mental health and more.

summaries.short: The combination of a win and homecoming provides the team with a boost before one of their biggest match-ups.
summaries.full: As the Panthers work to rebuild their bruised team morale, homecoming provides the players with some much-needed support before they take on IMG Academy's Ascenders – a fellow perennial powerhouse that shares a singular loss to Mater Dei – for the one of biggest football games Baltimore has ever seen.

summaries.short: With one week before the start of a grueling national schedule, Baltimore's St. Frances Academy Panthers trains on local streets and parks.
summaries.full: Only one week out from their season opener in Miami, Baltimore's St. Frances Academy Panthers prepare for their grueling upcoming national schedule. Lacking adequate facilities and forced out of their local private-school league after every opposing team forfeited to them, the team hits the streets to practice while reflecting on what football could mean for their futures.

summaries.short: Ahead of National Signing Day, St. Frances coaches meet with the seniors--both committed and uncommitted--to solidify their college plans.
summaries.full: As the final game of regular season looms, the Panthers' seniors are struck by the realization that their time at St. Frances is rapidly coming to a close and major life changes lie ahead. Before National Signing Day, Panthers' coaches aid in solidifying college plans and help place those still uncommitted, while surprises – some good, some less than – arise for the players.

summaries.full: Host Victor Cruz breaks down the first installment of HBO's The Cost of Winning, highlighting some memorable moments, and more. Then, Victor is joined by influential high fashion designer and legend in the hip-hop community, Dapper Dan, to talk about his path to success, overcoming challenges and advice he has for others looking to follow in his footsteps.
